Feature: MenuVC + PurchasesVC + TicketsVC unified admin-style redesign

Overview
- Define one shared redesign feature for `MenuVC`, `PurchasesVC` (requested as PurchesesVC), and `TicketsVC`.
- Apply the same visual system used by admin view controllers.
- Keep behavior, routes, payload contracts, and backend service usage unchanged.

Scope
- In scope: layout structure, component styling, hierarchy consistency, readability, and interaction affordances.
- Out of scope: endpoint/path changes, auth/header changes, payload key changes, and business-logic rewrites.

Prototype binding
- This specification is reviewed against:
  - `.ai/workflows/features/SwiftUIFeatures/prototypes/menuvc-purchasesvc-ticketsvc-adminstyle.prototype.html`

Functional requirements

REQ-MPT-1 Shared admin visual language
- Use the admin design baseline: rounded black top actions, grouped cards, subtle gray surface, clear section headers.
- Keep destructive emphasis only for destructive actions (for example, refund/cancel paths).

REQ-MPT-2 MenuVC structure and styling
- Keep top actions discoverable (`Back`, `Purchases`, optional `Admin` action depending on current role logic).
- Present profile and session data in grouped admin-style cards.
- Keep avatar/profile image visible and aligned with card content.

REQ-MPT-3 PurchasesVC structure and sorting UX
- Keep `Back`, sorting actions, and table content behavior unchanged.
- Restyle header actions and list rows to match admin card/list style.
- Preserve row swipe refund semantics and make the swipe affordance clear to users.
- Keep movie pictures visible in purchase rows.
- `Details` button is not needed in this redesign pass.

REQ-MPT-4 TicketsVC structure and action hierarchy
- Keep `Back` and `Pdf` actions present and primary.
- Keep ticket cards, QR area, and details readable in admin-style grouped sections.
- Preserve PDF preview/share/close flow behavior.

REQ-MPT-5 Interaction contracts and navigation
- Keep existing segue identifiers and destinations unchanged.
- Keep data-source and DataManager wiring unchanged for purchases/tickets retrieval and update.

REQ-MPT-6 Accessibility and touch targets
- Maintain readable text contrast and hierarchy.
- Buttons and row actions keep usable touch target sizes.

REQ-MPT-7 Reusable custom components (side-track)
- As a side part of this feature, implement reusable UI building blocks using existing iOS CustomCells patterns.
- Prefer existing reusable classes/patterns (`ListViewCell`, `FeedCells`, shared constraint helpers) over one-off per-screen row/button implementations.
- Define a reusable list-row style and reusable button style that can be shared by `MenuVC`, `PurchasesVC`, and `TicketsVC` redesign implementation.
- Keep original screen behaviors and service contracts unchanged while introducing reusable UI components.

Non-functional requirements

REQ-MPT-NF-1 Stability
- Existing menu -> purchases -> tickets flow must remain functionally equivalent.

REQ-MPT-NF-2 Performance
- Redesign should avoid repeated setup churn in appearance callbacks where possible.

Acceptance criteria
- [ ] One unified redesign feature covers `MenuVC`, `PurchasesVC`, and `TicketsVC`.
- [ ] Admin visual language is consistently applied across all three screens.
- [ ] Existing navigation, backend/service contracts, and action flows stay unchanged.
- [ ] Purchases rows clearly communicate swipe-to-refund and show movie pictures.
- [ ] Purchases prototype does not rely on a separate `Details` button.
- [ ] Reusable list-cell/button component track is included as an implementation deliverable for this feature.
- [ ] SVG artifacts exist for all three screens.
- [ ] HTML prototype exists and shows the three-screen flow with admin styling.

Reference files
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/MenuVC.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/PurchasesVC.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/TicketsVC.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/ListViewCell.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/FeedCells.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/UIViewExt.swift`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/menu-screen.svg`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/purchases-screen.svg`
- `SwiftCinemas/SwiftLoginScreen/tickets-screen.svg`
